        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Doctor: expose extra gateway service findings",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Exposes the extra gateway service doctor checks as structured health findings.\n- Adds dry-run repair effects for restart/retry actions that doctor already knows how to describe.\n- Keeps the existing `doctor:gateway-services` legacy run path authoritative for real normal `doctor` / `doctor --fix` behavior.\n- Declares the structured checks inline on the existing ordered doctor contribution, so core doctor ordering remains contribution-owned.\n\nThis is intentionally the gateway services slice from the doctor repair stack. It does not change gateway startup, provider config, or plugin health behavior.\n\n## Stack\n\nStacked on #86627. Current PR head is `52cd8cf69a06a9008a06acc558548a6de3742aa0`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed:\nExtra or legacy gateway-like services are now visible through structured doctor health checks, while normal mutating service cleanup remains owned by the existing `doctor:gateway-services` run path.\n\nReal environment tested:\nWSL Ubuntu 24.04, OpenClaw checkout `/root/src/openclaw-84340-proof`, PR head `52cd8cf69a06a9008a06acc558548a6de3742aa0`, source CLI via `node scripts/run-node.mjs`, isolated temp `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR`, temp `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH`, temp `HOME`, and a synthetic legacy user systemd unit at `$HOME/.config/systemd/user/clawdbot-gateway.service`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n1. Created an isolated temp config/state/workspace with local Gateway config and memory search disabled.\n2. Wrote `$HOME/.config/systemd/user/clawdbot-gateway.service` containing an `ExecStart` command with `clawdbot gateway` so the scanner sees a legacy gateway-like service.\n3. Ran `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=<temp>/state OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=<temp>/state/openclaw.json HOME=<temp>/home COREPACK_HOME=/root/.cache/node/corepack OPENCLAW_TEST_FAST=1 node scripts/run-node.mjs doctor --lint --json --only core/doctor/gateway-services/extra`.\n4. Ran focused validation: `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor-gateway-services.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts --reporter=dot`.\n5. Ran changed-file lint/checks: `pnpm exec oxlint src/commands/doctor-gateway-services.ts src/commands/doctor-gateway-services.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts` and `git diff --check`.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n```json\n{\n  \"lintStatus\": 1,\n  \"lintOk\": false,\n  \"lintChecksRun\": 1,\n  \"lintChecksSkipped\": 22,\n  \"legacyUnitExistsAfterLint\": true,\n  \"lintFindings\": [\n    {\n      \"checkId\": \"core/doctor/gateway-services/extra\",\n      \"severity\": \"warning\",\n      \"source\": \"linux\",\n      \"target\": \"clawdbot-gateway.service\",\n      \"fixHint\": \"Run openclaw doctor --fix to remove legacy gateway services.\",\n      \"message\": \"Other gateway-like service detected: clawdbot-gateway.service (user, unit: /tmp/openclaw-84340-proof-xX7FrA/home/.config/systemd/user/clawdbot-gateway.service)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nSupporting checks:\n- Focused Vitest: `src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts` 48 tests passed, `src/commands/doctor-gateway-services.test.ts` 33 tests passed.\n- `pnpm exec oxlint ...`: 0 warnings, 0 errors.\n- `git diff --check`: clean.\n- GitHub CI is green on current head, aside from non-blocking neutral CodeQL.\n\nObserved result after fix:\n`doctor --lint --json --only core/doctor/gateway-services/extra` reports the legacy gateway service as a structured warning with the expected check id, Linux source, target service label, and fix hint. Focused tests also cover the dry-run cleanup effect mapping for legacy gateway services and the no-effect behavior for intentional non-legacy extra services.\n\nWhat was not tested:\nThe proof uses a synthetic user systemd unit, not a real installed or running Gateway service. I did not run full `doctor --fix` service cleanup in WSL because the mutating cleanup path can invoke systemd/service-management behavior; the PR intentionally keeps that existing legacy run path authoritative.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor-gateway-services.test.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 81 tests passed across 2 shards\n- `pnpm exec oxlint src/commands/doctor-gateway-services.ts src/commands/doctor-gateway-services.test.ts src/flows/doctor-core-checks.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.ts src/flows/doctor-health-contributions.test.ts` -> 0 warnings, 0 errors\n- `git diff --check` -> clean\n",
